reviews.review: Great job undoing most of the nonsense of "The Worst Jedi."

Much better than expected after the damage done by TLJ.  Satisfying conclusion, but still left wondering what could have been if JJ Abrams had been in control from start to finish.  Story makes its way back into the Star Wars universe, but had to fight through the plot disaster of TLJ to get there.
I love all things Star Wars

As a standalone movie, i would rate it with 3,5 starts, as it is entertaining and visually amazing. However this is episode 9 of one of the greatest fantasy stories ever created in cinema. And as the last episode of this saga, in terms of story continuity and character development it is very disappointing and should receive 0.5 star. I gave it 2 stars as something in between both views. Some choices simply don't make sense considering the past films in the series. I believe this last trilogy should be separated from the other movies in the series. The Skywalker story ends with episode 6, The Return of the Jedi. This "Disney" trilogy is in general a very confusing series where characters are introduced, just to be ignored or removed in the nest movie not to mention certain "artistic liberties" done by both directors of this trilogy.
Let's hope the future of Star Wars is a better one with new and better stories and characters.
Clearly critics aren't fans. JJ Abrams gave us FANS what we wanted, and after all the Rocky movies and Fast and furious franchise it's a welcome finish.
I loved the humanity . It really became a story about nurture vs. nature. What defines family? All the loose ends were tied up. The CGI delivered.   I loved it
TROS was more of a sendoff tribute to the rest of the series (story and characters) and carried little in the way of its own story line.
It started off rather slow, but when it finally picked up it was great!  Loved the way they wrapped up most  of the story lines.
Like the previous two films in this trilogy, some good bits and some meh bits. Probably my favourite of the bunch though from what I can recall.
